[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
"Chi-chan?"[l][r]
A voice called out. I slowly turned around.[r]
Yuu was looking at me with concern in her eyes.[l][r]
After what happened yesterday, I didn’t think she’d come today. But here she was, like it was the most natural thing in the world.[l][r]

[r]"...Yuu..."[l][r]
The moment I looked at Yuu, something inside me burst.[r]
The emotions spilling out overwhelmed me like a landslide. They wouldn’t stop, and I didn’t want her to see them.[l][r]
But. I can't take it anymore. I’m at my limit.[l][r]
What limit? I don’t even know.[l][r]
It just hurts so much.[r]
It hurts so much![l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
"Sob… Yuu… Yuu!"[l][r]
"Chi-chan..."[l][r]
Yuu didn’t ask anything. Instead, she gently approached and held me tight.[l][r]
Her kindness felt so overwhelming, making me feel miserable. Why couldn't I just be honest? I wanted her to hate me, to get sick of my constant mood swings.[l][r]

[r]I hate it. It’s all lies. I don’t want her to hate me. But it hurts. Yet I’m happy. What is this feeling?[l][r]

[r]I don’t understand, I don’t understand, I don’t understand.[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
"I don't understand… I don’t understand anything!!"[l][r]
"Yeah"[l][r]
"Why are you so kind...? Just hate me already!"[l][r]
“I won't.”[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
Yuu hugged me tighter. She placed her hand on my head and gently stroked it, showing there was no lie in her actions.[l][r]
Receiving that, I must’ve panicked. Happiness, anger, sadness, confusion, joy, despair. Not just those, but so many other indescribable emotions filled me to the brim.[l][r]
It was Yuu who drove me to this madness. And only Yuu could heal me.[l][r]
[r]My everything. My Yuu.[l][r]
She was like a drug to me.[l][r]

[r]All I could do was keep longing for Yuu, desperately.[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

